<p>I am getting an error message from facebook. It says: Fatal error: Uncaught OAuthException: An active access token must be used to query information about the current user. It is catched on line 1265. On that line it is <code>$e = new FacebookApiException($result);</code> Would really need some help :)</p>  <pre><code> protected function throwAPIException($result) {          $e = new FacebookApiException($result);          switch ($e-&gt;getType()) {           // OAuth 2.0 Draft 00 style           case 'OAuthException':             // OAuth 2.0 Draft 10 style           case 'invalid_token':             // REST server errors are just Exceptions           case 'Exception':             $message = $e-&gt;getMessage();             if ((strpos($message, 'Error validating access token') !== false) ||                 (strpos($message, 'Invalid OAuth access token') !== false) ||                 (strpos($message, 'An active access token must be used') !== false)             ) {               $this-&gt;destroySession();              }             break;          }          throw $e;        } </code></pre>